column14: Tread steady and slow lest you end up below.
Cruel acts debase this tight space.
Smoothed stones hide bleached bones.
Worn hands etch an echoing stretch.
Each well drenched with rotting stench.
Men in fetters feed their betters.
The scent of death fills every breath.
Madness claws from inky maws.
Shadows choke; a lightless yoke.
Cold clay smothers decay.
They rot for ages in iron cages.
